subsection.def:
barrister
                    (大律師) has the same meaning as in the Legal
                Practitioners Ordinance (Cap. 159);

Registrar
                    (司法常務官) means the Registrar of the Court
                appointed under section 42;

paragraph.content:
the Chief Judge of the High Court, a Justice of Appeal or a judge of the
                    Court of First Instance;
                    or

if the judge’s term of office, as extended before the commencement date,
                    expires after the judge attains the age of 70 years—when the judge’s extended
                    term of office expires.

section.def:
appeal
                (上訴) means appeal to the Court in any civil cause
            or matter;

division.heading:
Appeal from Court of Appeal to Court;
            Appeal
            relating to
            Election;
            Appeal relating to Certain Proceedings

subparagraph.content:
an application for judicial review under section 21K of
                            the High Court Ordinance (Cap. 4);
                            or

an application for judicial review under section 21K of
                            the High Court Ordinance (Cap. 4);
                            or

an application for judicial review under section 21K of
                            the High Court Ordinance (Cap. 4);
                            or

an application for judicial review under section 21K of
                            the High Court Ordinance (Cap. 4);
                            or

subsection.content:
An application to the Court for leave to appeal shall be made within 28 days
                from the date of the decision of the Court of Appeal or the Court of First Instance,
                as the case may be. (Amended 120 of 1997 s. 13)
